43 SECTION 2.
44 Article 1 of Chapter 2 of Title 27 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
45 hunting, trapping, or fishing, is amended in Code Section 27-2-2, relating to issuance and
46 sale of hunting, fishing, and trapping licenses, withdrawal of agents' authority to sell licenses,
47 and optional participation in anatomical gift program, by revising subsection (d) as follows:
48 "(d) Prior to selling any license, except for a license sold over the telephone by an
49 approved telephone license agent or over the Internet internet by an approved Internet
50 internet license agent, each license agent shall require each person desiring to purchase a
51 license to display a driver's license in a physical format or equally reliable identification
52 of the individual and the current residence and age of such individual. In the event the
53 department determines that a license agent has intentionally or negligently sold a resident
54 license to a person who is a nonresident or who is underage, the department may
55 immediately withdraw the authority of such license agent to issue and sell licenses on
56 behalf of the department, provided that the department shall not withdraw the license
57 agent's authority until the license agent has been given ten days' written notice of intention
58 to withdraw authority setting forth the reason or reasons for the withdrawal and giving the
59 license agent a hearing in the county of said agent's residence on the reasons for
60 withdrawal."
61 SECTION 3.
